  "remediationDescription": "### Kubernetes\n\n1. Create purpose-specific namespaces for application, platform, and shared-service workloads.\n2. Move workloads out of the default namespace by updating the namespace field in manifests, Helm releases, or Kustomize overlays.\n3. Apply namespace-level labels, resource quotas, limit ranges, network policies, and Pod Security admission settings to the new namespaces.\n4. Update CI/CD deployment targets so new resources are not created in default.\n5. Review the default namespace and remove leftover application resources after migration.\n\nReference: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/namespaces/",
